### Not Found Handling

```typescript
// app/wallet/[id]/not-found.tsx
export default function NotFound() {
  return (
    <div>
      <h2>Wallet Not Found</h2>
      <p>The wallet you're looking for doesn't exist.</p>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Best Practices Summary

1. **Start with Server Components** - Only add 'use client' when needed
2. **Fetch data in parallel** - Use Promise.all to avoid waterfalls
3. **Cache strategically** - Use revalidate options appropriately
4. **Stream content** - Use Suspense for better UX
5. **Handle errors gracefully** - Create error boundaries
6. **Type everything** - Use explicit TypeScript types
7. **Optimize images** - Always use next/image
8. **Follow DRY** - Extract reusable logic
9. **Test critical paths** - Write tests for important features
10. **Monitor performance** - Use Core Web Vitals

